headline: Interactive Brokers (IBKR) Earnings Transcript
summary: In the fourth quarter, we continue to demonstrate the power and leverage of our diversified, fully automated global platform, which serves the full spectrum of investors from those new to the markets buying their first fractional share of a magnificent seven stock in a cash account, through sophisticated traders benefiting from low cost and geographical reach, to professionals using our APIs and algorithms to execute advanced quantitative strategies in portfolio margin accounts.  Client equity rose 37% to $780 billion, an increase of more than $200 billion year over year and the first time we have ended a year with over three-quarters of a trillion dollars in client assets.  Cyclically, rising markets and expectations for lower interest rates drive increased client engagement.

headline: Dow Jones Tumbles 871 Points On Trump's Greenland Threats; Nvidia, Tesla Skid As Netflix Falls Late

headline: Markets shrug off Interactive Brokers’ quarterly beat
summary: The automated global electronic broker posted adjusted earnings per share of $0.65, beating the analyst estimate of $0.59, while revenue reached $1.64 billion compared to the consensus estimate of $1.61 billion. Despite the beat on both metrics, the market reaction was decidedly negative.

headline: Interactive Brokers Tops Earnings Views, Shares Trade Near Entry

headline: Interactive Brokers’s (NASDAQ:IBKR) Q4 CY2025: Beats On Revenue
summary: Electronic brokerage firm Interactive Brokers (NASDAQ:IBKR) beat Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q4 CY2025, with sales up 15.4% year on year to $1.64 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.65 per share was 11% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

Interactive Brokers Earnings Will Show Just How Fast It Is  Growing Amid Bull Market for Stocks
summary: Wall Street analysts expect  Interactive Brokers  to report strong fourth-quarter earnings after the market closes Tuesday, reflecting a buoyant year for markets and a surge of retail investor trading.  Analysts anticipate Interactive Brokers will report adjusted fourth-quarter earnings of 59 cents per share on revenue of $1.6 billion, according to FactSet.  Shares of Interactive Brokers are up 48% over the past 12 months compared with a 13% gain for the S&P 500.
